records.addlTxt:
Defendant Vanessa M Garcia in court with attorney Michael Jude.  Defendant Vanessa M Garcia in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction with credit for 46 days time served; Huber privileges for work, child care and treatment.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 MONTHS.
Conditions: 
*  Participate in any counseling deemed appropriate by agent;
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate by agent;
*  Submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge;  payments to commence in July 8, 2016 at the rate of $25.00 per month or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Establish paternity;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety.

Court will waive all costs and surcharges that can be waived due to the defendant's inability to pay.  Court ordered restitution set at $0.00.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
